        <main class="docs-content">
            <h1>Settings & <span class="accent">Configuration</span></h1>
            <p>Customize GemCrest to match your business needs.</p>

            <h2>Shop Profile</h2>
            <p>Configure your shop's identity for invoices and reports:</p>

            <h3>Basic Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Shop Name:</strong> Appears on all invoices</li>
                <li><strong>Address:</strong> Full address with pincode</li>
                <li><strong>Phone:</strong> Primary contact number</li>
                <li><strong>Email:</strong> Business email address</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Tax Details</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>GST Number:</strong> Required for GST-compliant invoices</li>
                <li><strong>PAN:</strong> For tax documentation</li>
                <li><strong>State Code:</strong> Auto-detected from GST number</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Branding</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Logo:</strong> Upload your shop logo (PNG/JPG, max 500KB)</li>
                <li><strong>Invoice Header:</strong> Custom text above invoice</li>
                <li><strong>Invoice Footer:</strong> Terms, thank you message, etc.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Invoice Settings</h2>

            <h3>Invoice Numbering</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Prefix:</strong> e.g., "INV-", "GC-"</li>
                <li><strong>Starting Number:</strong> Next invoice number</li>
                <li><strong>Date Format:</strong> DD/MM/YYYY or MM/DD/YYYY</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Default Values</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Default Tax Rate:</strong> GST percentage (typically 3%)</li>
                <li><strong>Default Making Charge Type:</strong> Percentage or flat rate</li>
                <li><strong>Default Making Charge Value:</strong> Your standard making charge</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Purity Configuration</h2>
            <p>Set up the metal purities you work with:</p>

            <h3>Gold Purities</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>24K (999):</strong> 99.9% pure gold</li>
                <li><strong>22K (916):</strong> 91.6% pure gold</li>
                <li><strong>18K (750):</strong> 75% pure gold</li>
                <li><strong>14K (585):</strong> 58.5% pure gold</li>
            </ul>
            <p>You can add custom purities for specialized items.</p>

            <h3>Silver Purities</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>999 Silver:</strong> Fine silver</li>
                <li><strong>925 Silver:</strong> Sterling silver</li>
                <li><strong>800 Silver:</strong> German silver</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Making Charge Formula</h2>
            <p>Configure how making charges are calculated:</p>

            <h3>Percentage-Based</h3>
            <p>Making charge = (Metal Value × Percentage) / 100</p>
            <p>Example: ₹50,000 gold × 12% = ₹6,000 making charge</p>

            <h3>Per Gram</h3>
            <p>Making charge = Weight × Rate per gram</p>
            <p>Example: 10g × ₹500/g = ₹5,000 making charge</p>

            <h3>Flat Rate</h3>
            <p>Fixed making charge regardless of weight or value</p>

            <h2>Print Templates</h2>
            <p>Customize your invoice appearance:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Standard A4:</strong> Full-page professional layout</li>
                <li><strong>Typewriter:</strong> Classic typewriter-style format</li>
                <li><strong>Thermal:</strong> Compact for POS printers</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Backup & Restore</h2>
            <p>Protect your business data:</p>

            <h3>Creating a Backup</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Backup</strong></li>
                <li>Click "Create Backup"</li>
                <li>Choose save location (USB drive recommended)</li>
                <li>Backup file is created with timestamp</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Restoring from Backup</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Restore</strong></li>
                <li>Select your backup file</li>
                <li>Confirm restoration (this replaces current data)</li>
            </ol>

            <div class="callout callout-warning">
                <strong>Important:</strong> Create regular backups to protect against data loss. Store backups on a
                separate drive.
            </div>
        </main>
